    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-24T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="132"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/512: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-24T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 24, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>313. Your 535, October 24, 4 p.m. You are authorized to inform the British
                    Government that this Government accepts the invitation to be represented at a
                    conference to be held in London on the 2d of December<note n="83"
                        xml:id="d132fn83">By subsequent agreement among the interested Governments,
                        the opening date of the Conference was fixed at December 9, 1935.</note>
                    pursuant to the provisions of the Washington and London naval treaties.</p>
                <p>Please cable full text of the British Government’s communication with the
                    exception of the last paragraph quoted in your telegram under reference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
